{"id":"astro-ph/0108229","submitter":"Sushan Konar","authors":"Arnab Rai Choudhuri (IISc, Bangalore), Sushan Konar (IUCAA, Pune)","title":"Diamagnetic Screening of the Magnetic Field in Accreting Neutron Stars","comments":"Accepted in MNRAS. Final version to be published. Minor modifications\n  in the text, some numerical estimates corrected for","journal-ref":"Mon.Not.Roy.Astron.Soc. 332 (2002) 933","doi":"10.1046/j.1365-8711.2002.05362.x","report-no":"iucaa-39/2001","categories":"astro-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  A possible mechanism for screening of the surface magnetic field of an\naccreting neutron star, by the accreted material, is investigated. We model the\nmaterial flow in the surface layers of the star by an assumed 2-D velocity\nfield satisfying all the physical requirements. Using this model velocity we\nfind that, in the absence of magnetic buoyancy, the surface field is screened\n(submergence of the field by advection) within the time scale of material flow\nof the top layers. On the other hand, if magnetic buoyancy is present, the\nscreening happens over a time scale which is characteristic of the slower flow\nof the deeper (hence, denser) layers. For accreting neutron stars, this longer\ntime scale turns out to be about $10^5$ years, which is of the similar order as\nthe accretion time scale of most massive X-ray binaries.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 14 Aug 2001 07:51:55 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 27 Jan 2002 07:53:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
